# Cursor Rules for ioriens.github.io

## Project Overview
This is a personal navigation website project built with static HTML and developed using Gulp for building and development.

## Tech Stack
- HTML5
- CSS3
- JavaScript (ES6+)
- Gulp (Build Tool)
- Browser-sync (Development Server)

## Code Standards

### HTML
- Use semantic HTML tags
- Keep HTML structure clean and simple
- Inline CSS and JavaScript are allowed (project characteristic)
- Ensure all images have alt attributes
- Use UTF-8 encoding

### CSS
- Use concise CSS selectors
- Prioritize flexbox and grid layouts
- Maintain responsive design
- Use relative units (em, rem, %)
- Avoid excessive nesting

### JavaScript
- Use ES6+ syntax
- Keep code concise
- Avoid global variable pollution
- Use const and let instead of var

## File Structure
```
src/
├── index.html      # Main page
├── manifest.json   # PWA configuration
└── assets/         # Static resources
    ├── avatar.jpg
    ├── icons/
    └── social-icons/
```

## Development Workflow
- Use `pnpm run dev` to start development server
- Use `pnpm run build` to generate production files
- Modify files in src directory, build tools will handle automatically

## Code Style
- Use 2 spaces for indentation
- Use single quotes
- No semicolons at line end (JavaScript)
- Keep code concise, avoid over-engineering

## Performance Optimization
- Use appropriate image formats and sizes
- Minify HTML, CSS and JavaScript
- Use CDN for external resources
- Optimize critical rendering path

## Important Notes
- This is a simple personal website, keep code concise
- Don't over-design or add unnecessary features
- Keep loading speed fast
- Ensure proper display on different devices 